-- Stocks Erase Losses on Report of $20 Billion BP Escrow Deal
-- Michael P. Regan
-- 2010-06-16T16:08:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-16/u-s-stocks-erase-losses-on-report-of-20-billion-bp-escrow-deal-for-spill.html

          
          
             U.S. stock rose, erasing earlier
losses, after the New York Times reported that BP Plc has agreed
to place about $20 billion in escrow for claims related to the
Gulf of Mexico oil spill.  
 BP’s U.S. shares turned higher following the Times report
after earlier tumbling 5.8 percent.  
 The Standard & Poor’s 500 Index rose 0.2 percent to
1,117.08 at 12:05 p.m. in New York after tumbling as much as 0.7
percent earlier. The Dow Jones Industrial Average rose less than
1 point to 10,405.37 after tumbling 72 points earlier.  
          
          


  


        